title: Book and manage driving and riding tests for your pupils

heading_context: Book and manage driving and riding tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
If you’re an instructor or trainer, use this service to:

  • book car, motorcycle and other types of driving tests for your pupils
  • change, swap or cancel other types of appointments
  • confirm your pupil’s details before the test
  • manage your availability for car driving tests

You need your:

  • Government Gateway user ID and password
  • credit or debit card, or pre-funded account
  • pupil’s driving licence number when you book a car test, or confirm their details for other types of tests

This service is available from 6am to midnight.

You can book these types of driving tests:

  • car
  • motorcycle (module 1 and module 2)
  • lorry and bus, including the Driver Certificate of Professional Competence (CPC) part 3a, part 3b and part 4 tests

You must be registered to book tests.

heading_context: Book and manage driving and riding tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
You can book some tests up to 10 weeks in advance without giving your pupil’s details. This is known as ‘trainer booking’.

You can only do this for these types of tests:

  • motorcycle (module 1 and module 2)
  • lorry and bus, including the Driver CPC tests

You must confirm the pupil’s details by 9pm at least one clear working day before the test. Working days do not include Sundays and public holidays.

heading_context: Book and manage driving and riding tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
You must give at least 3 full working days’ notice to change or cancel a test, or you’ll have to pay again. Monday to Saturday count as working days but Sundays and public holidays do not.

Find out when you can get a refund if you change a driving test or cancel a driving test at short notice.

heading_context: Book and manage driving and riding tests for your pupils
chunks.html_content:
You may not be allowed to book trainer booking tests if you cancel either:

  • 25% or more of your tests
  • 20% or more of your tests within 10 clear working days of the test
